'''Epoxy''' was a fast-drying adhesive or protective coating used primarily to prevent a surface from rusting, usually found in the form of a paint.

==History==
One variant of epoxy was [[Corellian epoxy]].

During [[IG-88B/Legends|IG-88B's]] [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunting]] career, the [[Assassin droid/Legends|assassin droid]] was doused with an instant-hardening epoxy by a group of mercenaries loyal to a petty arms dictator named [[Grlubb]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Peridon's Folly]] in a desperate attempt to stop the [[Droid/Legends|droid's]] merciless onslaught. The epoxy temporarily succeeded in clogging IG-88's gears and servomotors, but the droid simply raised his body temperature to first melt the coating, and then bent his limbs to snap away the remains.<ref name="IG-88">{{StoryCite|story=Therefore I Am: The Tale of IG-88|book=Tales of the Bounty Hunters}}</ref>

The former [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtrooper]] [[Burrk]] used an instant-set epoxy found in the remains of [[Echo Base/Legends|Echo Base]] to craft makeshift spears made from metal shards to fend off a horde of attacking [[Wampa/Legends|wampas]] on the planet [[Hoth/Legends|Hoth]] in [[12 ABY/Legends|12 ABY]].<ref name="Darksaber">[[Darksaber (novel)|''Darksaber'']]</ref>

